<br>
I'm not going to get into the whole religion discussion again, but let me just say this, what makes your beliefs any better than anyone else? Or to turn the question on me, what makes mine any better than anyone elses? You believe things that can be "proven." Well there are a few debates on things that can be proven and things that can't. Take away a few of your senses, how well can you prove it then? Same goes for me, I can't prove it beyond a shadow of a doubt, but niether can you. I concur that some things you believe are true, but who is to say that some day in the future we'll find out that we were just being decieved?<br>
<br>
See, what I'm getting at here, is don't state your opinion as fact. Please. You propose your beliefs in a manner in which you say they're <i>obviously</i> correct and anyone who believes differently is living in a myth. That is my only beef with you. You are free to believe what you want, but don't insult others in the process.<br>
<br>
Oh, one more thing, I found this pretty funny:<br>
<br>
"I am no longer threatened to speak openly about my atheism. In the past, this could mean a loss of a job, and of friends, and a host of nasty things. Given time, people will come to understand atheism for what it is, and not what they would like it to be."<br>
<br>
Is this really true? Because I've heard numerous stories about Christians in the same position, losing their jobs, friends, etc. So they were closet Christians.<br>
<br>
